ImageList.ImageCollection Class

Definition

Encapsulates the collection of Image objects in an ImageList.

In this Article

[System.ComponentModel.Editor("System.Windows.Forms.Design.ImageCollectionEditor, System.Design, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a", typeof(System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditor))]
public sealed class ImageList.ImageCollection : System.Collections.IList
Inheritance
System.Object
ImageList.ImageCollection

Inherited Members

Equals(Object)
Equals(Object,Object)
GetHashCode()
GetType()
MemberwiseClone()
ReferenceEquals(Object,Object)
ToString()

Remarks

This is used to manage the images in the ImageList programmatically, providing methods to add and remove image objects.

Properties

Count

Gets the number of images currently in the list.

public int Count { get; }
Value
Int32

The number of images in the list. The default is 0.

Remarks

Counting the images forces the Handle to be created.

Empty

Gets a value indicating whether the ImageList has any images.

public bool Empty { get; }
Value
Boolean

true if there are no images in the list; otherwise, false. The default is false.

Remarks

You can check this property without forcing the creation of a Handle.

IsReadOnly

Gets a value indicating whether the list is read-only.

public bool IsReadOnly { get; }
Value
Boolean

Always false.

Item(Int32)

Gets or sets an Image at the specified index within the collection.

public System.Drawing.Image this[int index] { get; set; }
index
Int32

The index of the image to get or set.

Value
Image

The image in the list specified by index.

Exceptions
ArgumentOutOfRangeException

The index is less than 0 or greater than or equal to stem.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count*.

ArgumentException

image is not a Bitmap.

ArgumentNullException

The image to be assigned is null or not a Bitmap.

InvalidOperationException

The image cannot be added to the list.

Remarks

The returned bitmap is a copy of the original image and should be disposed of using the Dispose method.

Item(String)

Gets an Image with the specified key from the collection.

public System.Drawing.Image this[string key] { get; }
key
String

The name of the image to retrieve from the collection.

Value
Image

The Image with the specified key.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection. The key comparison is not case-sensitive.

If an image with the specified key is not found, the value of the Item property is null.

Keys

Gets the collection of keys associated with the images in the ImageList.ImageCollection.

public System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection Keys { get; }
Value
StringCollection

A StringCollection containing the names of the images in the ImageList.ImageCollection.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key, and an image key is not case-sensitive.

If none of the images contained in the ImageList.ImageCollection have keys, Keys returns an empty StringCollection.

Adds the specified icon to the ImageList.

public void Add (System.Drawing.Icon value);
value
Icon

An Icon to add to the list.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

value is null

-or-

value is not an Icon.

Remarks

The Icon is converted to a Bitmap before it is added to the list.

Adds the specified image to the ImageList.

public void Add (System.Drawing.Image value);
value
Image

A Bitmap of the image to add to the list.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

The image being added is null.

ArgumentException

The image being added is not a Bitmap.

Adds the specified image to the ImageList, using the specified color to generate the mask.

public int Add (System.Drawing.Image value, System.Drawing.Color transparentColor);
value
Image

A Bitmap of the image to add to the list.

transparentColor
Color

The Color to mask this image.

Returns
Int32

The index of the newly added image, or -1 if the image cannot be added.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

The image being added is null.

ArgumentException

The image being added is not a Bitmap.

Adds an icon with the specified key to the end of the collection.

public void Add (string key, System.Drawing.Icon icon);
key
String

The name of the icon.

icon
Icon

The Icon to add to the collection.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

icon is null.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection. An image key is not case-sensitive.

Add(String,Image)

Adds an image with the specified key to the end of the collection.

public void Add (string key, System.Drawing.Image image);
key
String

The name of the image.

image
Image

The Image to add to the collection.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

image is null.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection. An image key is not case-sensitive.

AddRange(Image[])

Adds an array of images to the collection.

public void AddRange (System.Drawing.Image[] images);
images
Image[]

The array of Image objects to add to the collection.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

images is null.

Remarks

Use ImageList.ImageCollection to add several images to the collection. To add a single item, use one of the Add methods.

AddStrip(Image)

Adds an image strip for the specified image to the ImageList.

public int AddStrip (System.Drawing.Image value);
value
Image

A Bitmap with the images to add.

Returns
Int32

The index of the newly added image, or -1 if the image cannot be added.

Exceptions
ArgumentException

The image being added is null.

-or-

The image being added is not a Bitmap.

InvalidOperationException

The image cannot be added.

-or-

The width of image strip being added is 0, or the width is not equal to the existing image width.

-or-

The image strip height is not equal to existing image height.

Remarks

The number of images to add is inferred from the width of the given image.

A strip is a single image that is treated as multiple images arranged side-by-side.

Clear()

Removes all the images and masks from the ImageList.

public void Clear ();

Contains(Image)

Not supported. The stem.Collections.IList.Contains* method indicates whether a specified object is contained in the list.

public bool Contains (System.Drawing.Image image);
image
Image

The Image to find in the list.

Returns
Boolean

true if the image is found in the list; otherwise, false.

Exceptions
NotSupportedException

This method is not supported.

Remarks

This implementation of the Contains method throws a NotSupportedException exception.

ContainsKey(String)

Determines if the collection contains an image with the specified key.

public bool ContainsKey (string key);
key
String

The key of the image to search for.

Returns
Boolean

true to indicate an image with the specified key is contained in the collection; otherwise, false.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key. The key comparison is not case-sensitive. If the key parameter is null or an empty string, the ContainsKey method returns false.

GetEnumerator()

Returns an enumerator that can be used to iterate through the item collection.

public System.Collections.IEnumerator GetEnumerator ();
Returns
IEnumerator

An IEnumerator that represents the item collection.

IndexOf(Image)

Not supported. The stem.Collections.IList.IndexOf* method returns the index of a specified object in the list.

public int IndexOf (System.Drawing.Image image);
image
Image

The Image to find in the list.

Returns
Int32

The index of the image in the list.

Exceptions
NotSupportedException

This method is not supported.

Remarks

This implementation of IndexOf throws a NotSupportedException exception.

IndexOfKey(String)

Determines the index of the first occurrence of an image with the specified key in the collection.

public int IndexOfKey (string key);
key
String

The key of the image to retrieve the index for.

Returns
Int32

The zero-based index of the first occurrence of an image with the specified key in the collection, if found; otherwise, -1.

Remarks

If IndexOfKey is called successively, the last returned index will be checked for a key match first, and if there is no match, the search starts at the beginning of the collection.

The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection. The key comparison is not case-sensitive. If the key parameter is null or an empty string, the IndexOfKey method returns -1.

Remove(Image)

Not supported. The stem.Collections.IList.Remove* method removes a specified object from the list.

public void Remove (System.Drawing.Image image);
image
Image

The Image to remove from the list.

Exceptions
NotSupportedException

This method is not supported.

Remarks

This implementation of Remove throws a NotSupportedException exception.

RemoveAt(Int32)

Removes an image from the list.

public void RemoveAt (int index);
index
Int32

The index of the image to remove.

Exceptions
InvalidOperationException

The image cannot be removed.

ArgumentOutOfRangeException

The index value was less than 0.

-or-

The index value is greater than or equal to the stem.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count* of images.

RemoveByKey(String)

Removes the image with the specified key from the collection.

public void RemoveByKey (string key);
key
String

The key of the image to remove from the collection.

Remarks

The key comparison is not case-sensitive. The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection.

SetKeyName(Int32,String)

Sets the key for an image in the collection.

public void SetKeyName (int index, string name);
index
Int32

The zero-based index of an image in the collection.

name
String

The name of the image to be set as the image key.

Exceptions
IndexOutOfRangeException

The specified index is less than 0 or greater than or equal to stem.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count*.

Remarks

The name of an image corresponds to its key in the ImageList.ImageCollection. An image key is not case-sensitive.

Copies the items in this collection to a compatible one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.

Exceptions

dest is null.

index is less than 0.

dest is multidimensional.

-or-

value

IList.IsFixedSize

Returns
